{"title_page": "2017 Iowa Hawkeyes football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode    = football\n| year    = 2017\n| team    = Iowa Hawkeyes\n| image   = Iowa Hawkeyes wordmark.svg\n| image_size = 250\n| conference = Big Ten Conference\n| division =West Division\n| short_conf = Big Ten\n| APRank  = \n| CoachRank =\n| CFPRank   = \n| record  = 8\u20135\n| conf_record = 4\u20135\n| head_coach = [[Kirk Ferentz]]\n| hc_year  = 19th\n| off_coach = [[Brian Ferentz]]\n| oc_year  = 1st season as OC; 6th overall\n| def_coach = [[Phil Parker]]\n| dc_year  = 6th season as DC; 19th overall\n| captain =\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = [[4\u20133 defense|4\u20133]]\n| stadium = [[Kinnick Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 70,585)\n| champion= Pinstripe Bowl champion\n| bowl = [[2017 Pinstripe Bowl|Pinstripe Bowl]]\n| bowl_result = W 27\u201320 vs. [[2017 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]]\n}}\n{{2017 Big Ten football standings}}\nThe '''2017 Iowa Hawkeyes football team''' represented the [[University of Iowa]] in the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Hawkeyes, led by 19th-year head coach [[Kirk Ferentz]], were members of the West Division of the [[Big Ten Conference]] and played their home games at [[Kinnick Stadium]] in [[Iowa City, Iowa]]. They finished the season 8\u20135, 4\u20135 in [[2017 Big Ten Conference football season|Big Ten play]] to finish in a tie for third place in the West Division. They received an invite to the [[2017 Pinstripe Bowl|Pinstripe Bowl]] where they defeated [[2017 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]].\n\nThe Iowa football program was awarded [[Disney's Wide World of Sports Spirit Award]] for the [[Iowa Hawkeyes football#Kinnick Wave|Kinnick Wave]], a new tradition that began during the season, where, at the end of the first quarter of every home game everyone in the stadium turned and waved to the young patients watching from the Stead Family Children's Hospital, which overlooks Kinnick Stadium.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thegazette.com/subject/sports/university-of-iowas-kinnick-wave-wins-disney-sports-spirit-award-20171121|title=University of Iowa's 'Kinnick Wave' wins Disney Sports Spirit Award {{!}} The Gazette|work=The Gazette|access-date=2018-01-25}}</ref> This season marked the first time since 1980 that the Tigerhawk logo was displayed at midfield in Kinnick Stadium.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kinnick Stadium Field Design Will Feature Tigerhawk |url=http://www.hawkeyesports.com/news/2017/6/12/football-kinnick-stadium-field-design-will-feature-tigerhawk.aspx |work=University of Iowa Athletic Department |date=June 12, 2017 |accessdate=September 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbssports.com/college-football/news/look-iowa-puts-logo-at-midfield-of-kinnick-stadium-after-nearly-40-years-without-one/|title=LOOK: Iowa puts logo at midfield of Kinnick Stadium after nearly 40 years without one|work=CBSSports.com|access-date=2018-01-25|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Previous season ==\nThe [[2016 Iowa Hawkeyes football team|Hawkeyes]] finished the [[2016 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2016 season]] 8\u20135, 6\u20133 in [[2016 Big Ten Conference football season|Big Ten play]] to finish in second place in the West Division. They received an invite to the [[2017 Outback Bowl|Outback Bowl]] where they lost to [[2016 Florida Gators football team|Florida]].\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===Recruiting===\n\n====Position key====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[Running back|Back]]\n|'''B'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Center (American football)|Center]]\n|'''C'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Cornerback]]\n|'''CB'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Defensive back]]\n|'''DB'''\n|-\n|[[Defensive end]]\n|'''DE'''\n|[[Defensive lineman]]\n|'''DL'''\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|'''DT'''\n|[[End (American football)|End]]\n|'''E'''\