 those matchups was a trip to [[Ames, Iowa|Ames]] for the annual [[Iowa\u2013Iowa State football rivalry|Cy-Hawk rivalry game]] against the [[Iowa State Cyclones football|Iowa State Cyclones]] from the [[Big 12 Conference]].\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\n| poll = [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 2\n| time = 11:00 a.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Wyoming Cowboys football team|Wyoming]]\n| site_stadium = [[Kinnick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Iowa City, Iowa|Iowa City, IA]]\n| tv = [[Big Ten Network|BTN]]\n| score = 24\u20133\n| attend = 68,075\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 9\n| time = 11:00 a.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Iowa State Cyclones football team|Iowa State]]\n| gamename = [[Iowa\u2013Iowa State football rivalry|Cy-Hawk Trophy]]\n| site_stadium = [[Jack Trice Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Ames, Iowa|Ames, IA]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football|ESPN2]]\n| score = 44\u201341\n| overtime = OT\n| attend = 61,500\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 16\n| time = 2:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 North Texas Mean Green football team|North Texas]]\n| site_stadium = Kinnick Stadium\n| site_cityst = Iowa City, IA\n| tv = ESPN2\n| score = 31\u201314\n| attend = 65,668\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 23\n| time = 6:30 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]]\n| opprank = 4\n| site_stadium = Kinnick Stadium\n| site_cityst = Iowa City, IA\n| tv = [[Saturday Night Football|ABC]]\n| score = 19\u201321\n| attend = 66,205\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 30\n| time = 3:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Michigan State Spartans football team|Michigan State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Spartan Stadium (East Lansing)