ai Films]] <br> Delhi Dot Com\n| [[Cinema of France|France]] <br> [[Cinema of Germany|Germany]] <br> [[Cinema of Italy|Italy]] <br> [[Cinema of the United States|United States]]\n| [[Mira Nair]]\n| $22.45&nbsp;million\n| {{sort|01.1|}} {{INR}}1.1&nbsp;billion\n| {{sort|03.12|}} {{INR}}3.12&nbsp;billion (US$48&nbsp;million)\n| {{#tag:ref|''Monsoon Wedding'' {{ndash}} {{US$|22.45 million}}, which in Indian rupees was {{INRConvert|110.01|c|year=2001}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pacific Exchange Rate Service (49 INR per USD)|url=http://fx.sauder.ubc.ca/etc/USDpages.pdf#page=3|website=[[UBC Sauder School of Business]]|publisher=[[University of British Columbia]]|page=3|year=2002|accessdate=21 November 2017}}</ref>\n*United States {{ndash}} $13,885,966<ref>{{cite web|title=Monsoon Wedding|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=monsoonwedding.htm|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=18 June 2011}}</ref>\n*Other territories {{ndash}} $8,564,778<ref name=\"monsoon\">{{cite web|title=Monsoon Wedding (2002) - International Box Office Results|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=monsoonwedding.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=3 September 2003|accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>\n|group=n|name=Monsoon}}\n|-\n| 6\n| ''[[Adventures of Ali-Baba and the Forty Thieves (1980 film)|Alibaba Aur 40 Chor]]''\n| 1980\n| Eagle Films <br> [[Uzbekfilm]]\n| [[Cinema of the Soviet Union|Soviet Union]]\n| Latif Faiziyev <br> [[Umesh Mehra]]\n| {{US$|20.5 million|long=no}}\n| {{sort|00.221|}} {{INR|221 million}}\n| {{sort|03.97|}} {{INR|3.97 billion}} ({{US$|61 million}})\n| {{#tag:ref|''Alibaba Aur 40 Chor'' in the Soviet Union {{ndash}} 52.8{{nbsp}}million box office admissions,<ref name=\"Kudryavtsev\">{{cite web|url=http://kinanet.livejournal.com/14172.html|title=\u041e\u0442\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0444\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043c\u044b \u0432 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u043a\u0438\u043d\u043e\u043f\u0440\