 of Verse in Adversity|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=January 4, 1981|page=A1}}</ref>\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"McKenzie, Floretta D.\"|Floretta D. McKenzie || data-sort-value=\"1981-01-03\"|July 1, 1981&nbsp;\u2013 February 8, 1988 || || data-sort-value=\"f\"|<ref>{{cite news|last=Valente|first=Judith|title=McKenzie Named D.C. School Chief|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=June 18, 1981|page=A1}}</ref><ref name=mckenzieresigns>{{cite news|title=Acting D.C. School Chief Named|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=January 29, 1988|page=C4}}</ref>\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Jenkins, Andrew E.\"|Andrew E. Jenkins || data-sort-value=\"1988-05-25\"|May 25, 1988&nbsp;\u2013 May 15, 1991 || data-sort-value=\"1988-02-09\"|February 9, 1988&nbsp;\u2013 May 24, 1988 (acting) || data-sort-value=\"g\"|<ref name=mckenzieresigns /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sanchez|first1=Rene|last2=Pink|first2=Daniel H.|title=Insider Jenkins to Head D.C. Schools|work=The Washington Post|date=May 25, 1988|page=A1|postscript=none}}; {{cite news|last1=Sanchez|first1=Rene|last2=Pink|first2=Daniel H.|title=Jenkins to Stay On for Final Year|work=The Washington Post|date=July 13, 1990|page=A1}}</ref><ref name=franklinhired />\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Smith, Franklin L.\"|Franklin L. Smith || data-sort-value=\"1991-05-15\"|May 15, 1991&nbsp;\u2013 November 4, 1996 || || data-sort-value=\"h\"|<ref name=franklinhired>{{cite news|last=Richardson|first=Lynda|title=D.C. Schools Chief to Make $131,000|work=The Washington Post|date=May 16, 1991|page=C3}}</ref><ref name=franklinfired />\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Becton, Julius W. Jr.\"|[[Julius W. Becton, Jr.]] || data-sort-value=\"1996-11-05\"|November 5, 1996&nbsp;\u2013 March 26, 1998 || || data-sort-value=\"i\"|<ref name=franklinfired>{{cite news|last=Vise|first=David|title=D.C. Control Board to Oust Superintendent, Sources Say|work=The Washington Post|date=November 6, 1996|page=D1}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Wilgoren|first1=Debbi|last2=Loeb|first2=Vernon|title=